CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 4, 1956, page A11, reads: "'Having Fun?'... asks Roland Sawyer, president of the Frogs, as he talks with this quartet of lovely young visitors at the sons and daughters of Frogs' party Monday night. Left to right: Iris Cornelis, Washington, D. C.; Willie Coram, Yonkers, N. Y.; Mr. Sawyer, Jacqueline McNeil, Nashville, Tenn., and Shirley Yvonne Larkin, Beaumont, Tex. The girls are visiting college friends in Pittsburgh. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Iris Cornelis, Willie Coram, Roland M. Sawyer, Jacqueline McNeil, and Shirley Yvonne, posed on the Loendi Club porch for FROGS week event
